  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Primary: We hypothesize a clinically significant improvement in sleep latency, sleep-onset
      and total sleep time measures in adults with ADHD when given a trial of Ramelteon compared to
      placebo. Secondary:We expect that Ramelteon will show statistically significant improvements
      vs. placebo in measures of daytime sleepiness and with no decrement in daytime functioning,
      including such specific items as focus and social and occupational functioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Method: 8-week, randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled crossover trial of Ramelteon in
      adult ADHD subjects who suffer from initial insomnia.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
